product_name: Anastasia Beverly HillsBrow Definer 3-in-1 Triangle Tip Easy Precision Eyebrow Pencil Mini
summary: SummaryHighlightsCruelty FreeThe Anastasia Beverly Hills Deluxe Mini Brow Definer, an all-in-one triangular-tipped pencil for defining, filling and detailing brows.
details: DetailsFeaturesThe triangular tip showcases three different-sized edges, which is ideal for multifunctional use and versatility in applicationUse the flat side for shading and outlining the brows. Use the medium side to fill and define. Use the fine tip to create hairlike detailFormula features the perfect balance of wax and pigment for easy blending and application (without skipping)Blend with a spoolie brush for a natural-looking finishAvailable in 12 shadesBenefitsCruelty-freeShadesBlonde - For Blonde hair with warm/gold undertonesTaupe - For Blonde hair with cool/ash undertonesAuburn - For Red hair with a dark undertoneCaramel - For Red hair with a light undertoneStrawburn - For light red hair with a warm undertoneDark Brown - For Dark Brown hair with a warm undertoneChocolate - For Medium Brown hair with warm/gold undertonesSoft Brown - For Light Brown hair with warm/cool undertonesAsh Brown - For grey hair with cool/ash undertonesEbony - For Black hair with a warm undertoneMedium Brown - For Medium Brown hair with cool/ash undertonesGranite - For Black hair with a cool undertoneItem 2618195How To UseHOW TO APPLYBegin by exposing only a small bit of product (about 2--3 millimeters); this allows for maximum control of the pencil and prevents overextension when applying the product. Remember all ABH products are highly pigmented, so little pressure is required.Start by defining the brow shape. Comb the hairs upward with the spoolie. Then, using the flat side of the pencil tip, outline the bottom of the brow from arch to tail. Next, comb the hairs downward and outline the top of the brow from arch to tail with the flat side. Comb the hairs back in place and fill in the brow from arch to tail using the medium side of the tip. Next, detail the front of the brow by creating hairlike strokes using the fine tip. Starting at the base of the front of the brow, press the tip down and pull up in the direction of the hair's natural growth. Use this technique in areas where there is empty space. Continuously blend throughout.PRO TIPS路Use the fine tip to create hairlike strokes by applying light pressure and swiping in the direction that hair grows naturally.路Perfect for quick, on-the-go application, use the flat side of the pencil to outline the top and the bottom of the brow, then shade in the center.路Keep Brow Definer sharp by lightly swiping the tip on a piece of paper. Start by exposing a small amount of product, then gently run the widest slant side of the pencil in an up-and-down motion on a flat sheet of paper. This will restore its shape and refresh the tip and sides.IngredientsBehenic Acid, Rhus Succedanea Fruit Wax/Cera, Lanolin, Triethylhexanoin, Sucrose Tetrastearate Triacetate, Hydrogenated Castor Oil, Sorbitan Sesquiisostearate, Hydrogen Dimethicone, Caprylyl Glycol, Hexylene Glycol, Phenoxyethanol, Tocopherol, May Contain/Peut Contenir (+/-): Mica, Iron Oxides (CI 77491, CI 77492, CI 77499), Titanium Dioxide (CI 77891)Shipping & Coupon RestrictionsThis brand is excluded from most Ulta Beauty coupons.See brand eligibility details
how_to_use: HOW TO APPLYBegin by exposing only a small bit of product (about 2--3 millimeters); this allows for maximum control of the pencil and prevents overextension when applying the product. Remember all ABH products are highly pigmented, so little pressure is required.Start by defining the brow shape. Comb the hairs upward with the spoolie. Then, using the flat side of the pencil tip, outline the bottom of the brow from arch to tail. Next, comb the hairs downward and outline the top of the brow from arch to tail with the flat side. Comb the hairs back in place and fill in the brow from arch to tail using the medium side of the tip. Next, detail the front of the brow by creating hairlike strokes using the fine tip. Starting at the base of the front of the brow, press the tip down and pull up in the direction of the hair's natural growth. Use this technique in areas where there is empty space. Continuously blend throughout.PRO TIPS路Use the fine tip to create hairlike strokes by applying light pressure and swiping in the direction that hair grows naturally.路Perfect for quick, on-the-go application, use the flat side of the pencil to outline the top and the bottom of the brow, then shade in the center.路Keep Brow Definer sharp by lightly swiping the tip on a piece of paper. Start by exposing a small amount of product, then gently run the widest slant side of the pencil in an up-and-down motion on a flat sheet of paper. This will restore its shape and refresh the tip and sides.

reviews.headline: The shade I've been looking for my entire life
reviews.comments:
I finally found the perfect ash brown shade that I have been looking years for.  I'm talking years of going without an eyebrow pencil because every shade out there was just wrong for me.  
The pencil itself has a wider diameter which makes it more comfortable to use. The tip is thick triangle that allows you to apply easier without needing much product. The brush is thick and does a beautiful job.  Don't let the price scare you - it's worth every penny! わ

reviews.headline: I will buy this again.
reviews.comments: Great product.  The color is perfect. I am so glad my salesperson recommended this product.

reviews.headline: Irreplaceable
reviews.comments: I have extremely mismatched, uneven, and just an overall unattractive pair of eyebrows. They are a major insecurity of mine and I struggled for quite a few years looking for some kind of solution to help with them. This is the only product I have found that completely and effortlessly makes a night and day difference with them. Super easy to work with, pencil glides smoothly, convenient spoolie, and color is very natural looking but buildable if a more dramatic look is needed. Amazing quality and I have always gotten quite a bit of use out of mine before needing to replace it. Price is on the higher end but for the quality and length in between replacing it is more than worth it.

faceoff_positive.comments:
Let me start by saying- I do not own the brow wiz or any other brow pencil. Why? Because they all have always seemed too dry, too hard and the small round tip they all have, seems to be ill shaped for what it is meant to be used for. I have always used brow powders/mousses/pomades. I also do not have "instagram" brows. My brows a already shaped and decently full, I just use brow products to define and darken, since my hair is colored much darker than my natural color (see picture for reference). 

Anyways- I picked this up as I was getting tired of my usual brow products and the shape of this intrigued me. I have been using it for about 2-3 weeks and am very happy with it. I love the angled tip which allows me to draw even lines of all shapes and sizes and to quickly fill in large spaces. I can make the lines lighter or darker, depending on how hard I press and if I press too hard, the bristled end does a great job of "fixing" the issue. I don't understand why some reviewers consider this large and chunky? Maybe b/c they are used to using a tiny dot sized brown pencil? Heck if I know. This hasn't dried out at all nor has it wore down much. I still have a lot of product left AND this item is more than twice the amount of product you get with the brow wiz (0.003 vs. 0.007)(see attached pic). It also doesn't flake or crumble during application and the color does not fade during the day. Overall, excellent brow product that I will continue to use.
faceoff_positive.headline: Better than the rest

faceoff_negative.comments: Let me start by saying I'm the biggest fan of AB pomade. It's the only thing I trust on these brows and has NEVER failed me. Since I love AB I thought I'd try out one of their brow pencils for a quicker application, but which one-  Brow Wiz or Brow Definer?  I watched all the Youtube videos, read all the reviews, and decided the brow definer was the one. I was so excited to try it and man was I so terribly disappointed. The pencil reminds me of the very bottom of the pomade when it's dried and crumbly. I have to apply so much pressure when using this pencil that I've literally taken out brow hairs with every pass. Faint color, product feels dry, and the triangular tip feels too big and does nothing to give my brows shape. I wish I didn't spend money on this product.
faceoff_negative.headline: Very Disappointed
